The Secure Contract Signing protocol of [[Main Page|SXP]] is a [[Protocols|Protocol]].

'''Current status: It remains to be defined. It is the first important technical task ahead of us.'''

== What should it do? ==
Allow several parties to sign a contract securely.
* But what do we mean by secure in this case?
* Are we going to rely on a Trusted Third Party?

